r once, but it is a larger behavioral change than a data-write repair.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"middle\",\n          \"reason\": \"The change is confined to the due-diligence loop in the middle part of the process.\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"best_resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS2_move_evaluation_extra_decision_before_loop\",\n  \"best_resolution_reason\": \"RS2 is recommended because it fully resolves the violation while preserving the intended meaning of 'evaluation_extra' as a decision variable for whether extra due diligence is required. Unlike RS1, it avoids leaving the loop condition without an explicit prior producer in the process. Unlike RS3, it does not restructure the process or change the loop execution semantics. It is localized, low cost, and consistent with the existing compliant requirements R1 and R3.\"\n}",
